I stumble across this question and needed a solution as well,
after reading thru the [javadocs][1] here&#39;s how you can read the defined interval. 
It&#39;s important to note that there are different types of triggers, assuming you&#39;re using the *SimpleScheduleBuilder* for creating triggers you can do the following:

    for(Trigger trigger : getAllTrigersFromSchduler()) {
		System.out.println(trigger.getDescription());	// for description
		// assuming a SimpleTrigger
		System.out.println(((SimpleTrigger)trigger).getRepeatInterval()));	// for interval in ms as long
	}

regards

  [1]: https://www.quartz-scheduler.org/api/2.2.1/org/quartz/SimpleTrigger.html

