In mathematics and programming, trigonometric functions like cos typically expect angles to be in radians, not degrees. In your case, when you used Math.cos(579.894), you were providing an angle in radians, which resulted in the incorrect answer.

To fix this, you should convert your angle from degrees to radians before passing it to the Math.cos function. Here&#39;s how you can do it in Kotlin:

    import kotlin.math.cos
    import kotlin.math.toRadians

    fun main(){
        val degrees = 579.894
        val radians = Math.toRadians(degrees)
        val result = cos(radians)
        println(result)
    }
